Plate Reader 4: 20230321

Test WT KN99-alpha and GAT201 deletion mutant 003(Madhani), BLP2 deletion mutant, CFO1 deletion mutant and BLP4 deletion mutant, CFO1 deletion mutant in RPMI at 37 degrees. 4 Bioreps, 3 Techreps each. Grow 5ml culture from colony (1 colony = 1 Biorep) in YPD, 30C, 180 rpm ON. Seed at OD 600nm = 0.2 , 200 ul per well. Run for 2 days (300 cycles).

library("reshape2")
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyverse)
library(rmarkdown)
library(cowplot)
library(yaml)
library(knitr)

Read in transposed data as csv file RPMI

rawdata <- read.csv("../Input/20230321_RPMI_Gat201Targets_Plate4_csv.csv")

Change time in seconds to time in days RPMI

 rawdata_day<-mutate(rawdata, Time = Time/86400)

Tidy the data using the melt function from reshape2 RPMI

reshaped <- melt(rawdata_day, id=c("Time", "Temp"), 
                              variable.name="Well",
                              value.name="OD595")

Combine the reshaped data with the plate map, pairing them by Well

annotated <- inner_join(reshaped, platemap, by="Well")

How stable are ODs of blank wells, to use for normalisation? RPMI

ggplot(data=filter(annotated, is.na(Strain)),
          aes(x=Time, y=OD595,  group = Well)) + 
          geom_line() + 
          labs(x="Time (days)", y="Absorbance at 595 nm")

ggplot(data=filter(annotated,Well=="G12"), 
       aes(x=Time, y=OD595, group = Well)) + 
 
       geom_line() + 
     theme_bw()+
     labs(x="Time (hrs)", y="Absorbance at 595 nm")

Remove well A2-7, H2-10, B1,D1,F1

Calculate median OD for blank wells for each growth medium RPMI

blank_OD_summary <- annotated %>%
   filter(is.na(Strain), Time < 1/24) %>%
  filter(Well != "A1") %>%
  filter(Well != "A2") %>%
  filter(Well != "A3") %>%
  filter(Well != "A4") %>%
  filter(Well != "A5") %>%
  filter(Well != "A6") %>%
  filter(Well != "A7") %>%
  filter(Well != "B1") %>%
  filter(Well != "D1") %>%
  filter(Well != "F1") %>%
  filter(Well != "H2") %>%
  filter(Well != "H4") %>%
  filter(Well != "H5") %>%
  filter(Well != "H6") %>%
  filter(Well != "H7") %>%
  filter(Well != "H8") %>%
  filter(Well != "H9") %>%
  filter(Well != "H10") %>%
    group_by(Media) %>%
  summarise(OD_median=median(OD595),
            OD_mean=mean(OD595),
            OD_max=max(OD595),
            OD_min=min(OD595))
print(blank_OD_summary)
## # A tibble: 1  5
##   Media OD_median OD_mean OD_max OD_min
##   <chr>     <dbl>   <dbl>  <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 R         0.113   0.111  0.119  0.101

Subtract blank OD to make corrected OD and Plot OD_corrected v Time (hrs) RPMI

normalisedOD <- annotated %>%
              left_join(blank_OD_summary, by="Media") %>%
              mutate(OD_corrected = OD595 - OD_median)

Plot OD all RPMI

ggplot(data=normalisedOD %>%
                       filter( !is.na(Strain) ), 
                      aes(x=Time, y=OD_corrected, color=Strain, group = Well)) + 
       geom_line() + 
       scale_y_continuous(limits=c(0,0.17),expand=c(0,0))+
       facet_wrap(Strain ~ .)+
  
       labs(x = "Time(Hrs)",
            y = "Absorbance (595nm)") +
       theme(text = element_text(size = 20))+
       theme_bw()+
       scale_color_brewer(palette="Set1")

Plot OD cfo1 RPMI

ggplot(data=normalisedOD %>%
                      filter(Strain == "cfo1"), 
                      aes(x=Time, y=OD_corrected, ccolour=Biorep, group = Well)) + 
       geom_line() + 
       scale_y_continuous(limits=c(0,0.18),expand=c(0,0))+
              labs(x = "Time(Hrs)",
            y = "Absorbance (595nm)") +
       theme(text = element_text(size = 20))+
       theme_bw()+
       scale_color_brewer(palette="Set1")

Plot OD all stat_summary(geom -line) remove excess lines RPMI

ggplot(data=normalisedOD  %>%
    #dplyr::mutate(Strain = factor(Strain, levels = c("KN99 (WT)","GAT201","BLP2","BLP4","CFO1")))%>%
                     filter( !is.na(Strain) ),  
                      aes(x=Time, y=OD_corrected, color=Strain)) + 
       stat_summary(fun = "median", geom = "line", size = 1) +
       scale_y_continuous(limits=c(0,0.15),expand=c(0,0), breaks = c(0, 0.05, 0.15)) +
  
       labs(x = "Number of Days",
            y = "Absorbance (595nm)",
            title = "GAT201 Targets", subtitle = "Plate 4: RPMI at 37 degrees") +
       theme_bw() +
       theme(text = element_text(size = 15))+
       theme(axis.title = element_text(size = 15))+
       theme(axis.ticks.length = unit(0.3, "cm"))+
       theme(title = element_text(size = 15))+
       theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
       theme(legend.title = element_text(size = 15))+
      theme(legend.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent", color=NA))+
  theme(legend.key = element_rect(fill = "transparent", color=NA))+
       theme (plot.background =  element_rect(fill = "transparent", color=NA), 
         panel.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent", color=NA),)+
      theme(panel.border = element_rect(linetype = "solid", colour = "black", size = 2))+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5) )+
       scale_color_brewer(palette="Set1")

ggsave("../Results/AllSummaryPR4.png",width = 6.6,height=5)
